# Sky Framework Conventions

## Language & Style
- C11, ESP-IDF v5.x, PlatformIO build system
- All public symbols prefixed `sky_` (framework) or `luxia_` (product)
- Error return: always `esp_err_t`; use `ESP_ERROR_CHECK()` for fatal init
- Logging: `ESP_LOG{I,W,E,D}(TAG, ...)` with `static const char *TAG = "sky_<component>"`

## Component Structure
```
components/sky_<name>/
├── CMakeLists.txt     # idf_component_register(SRC_DIRS "src" INCLUDE_DIRS "include" REQUIRES sky_core)
├── Kconfig            # menu "Sky <Name>" ... endmenu
├── include/sky_<name>.h
└── src/sky_<name>.c
```

## Init Pattern
Every component follows: `init(config) → start() → stop() → deinit()`
- `init` is idempotent (returns `ESP_ERR_INVALID_STATE` if already initialized)
- Register with `sky_registry` for lifecycle management
- Default config via `SKY_<NAME>_CONFIG_DEFAULT()` macro

## Events
- Publish via `sky_event_publish(SKY_EVENT_*, &data, sizeof(data))`
- Subscribe via `sky_event_subscribe(SKY_EVENT_*, handler, ctx)`
- Event IDs reserved by range: core 0x00xx, stepper 0x01xx, network 0x02xx, OTA 0x028x, power 0x03xx

## NVS
- Use `sky_config_set_*/get_*` with short namespace strings (≤15 chars)
- Never write NVS in hot loops; persist on state change only

## Thread Safety
- Protect shared state with FreeRTOS mutex
- Use queues for inter-task commands (stepper, OTA)
- Never call `sky_event_publish` while holding a component mutex
